                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14214814" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:35:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://datastax-oss.atlassian.net/browse/PYTHON-185&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://datastax-oss.atlassian.net/browse/PYTHON-185&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14214821" author="snazy" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 16:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8261&quot; title=&quot;Clean up schema metadata classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8261&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8261&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (currently ongoing schema table refactoring)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14215055" author="philipthompson" created="Mon, 17 Nov 2014 19:42:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This python driver issue is also breaking 90% of dtests on trunk, which will also be fixed once a 2.1.3 python driver release is out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14215468" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2014 00:16:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW the python driver shouldn&apos;t be needing the alias columns since 2.0, and index_interval since 2.1. And &lt;b&gt;all&lt;/b&gt; of these tables will be gone after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6717&quot; title=&quot;Modernize schema tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6717&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6717&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14216519" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2014 18:02:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, for the record, in this particular case I was wrong to push that ninja-commit, despite the fact that all of those schema tables will be disappearing entirely in 3.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aside from cqlsh, CqlRecordWriter was for some reason still taking its columns info from key_aliases and column_aliases. All using Thrift, too. Will fix that separately this time instead of reverting the patch, though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry about all that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14216833" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2014 21:39:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed a temporary fix to the bundled python driver as 3cc9a0c.  You can find the branch that corresponds to the committed version here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/thobbs/python-driver/tree/CASSANDRA-8326-temp-fix&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/thobbs/python-driver/tree/CASSANDRA-8326-temp-fix&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not a final fix, it&apos;s just enough to get cqlsh working for now, so this ticket will remain open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14252013" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 18 Dec 2014 18:40:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The python driver has been upgraded to 2.1.3 as commit d2583ce, so this is fixed now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
